summary:
their first kiss takes place on the statue of liberty.
they are nineteen, they meet only two weeks and are still rarely chosen...
body:
headcanon without superpowers

their first kiss takes place on the statue of liberty.

they are nineteen, they meet only two weeks and are still rarely chosen somewhere together.

that day it is overcast but warm. johnny writes to peter and offers to make a small trip through times square - after all, even new yorkers should sometimes get out on the streets of their hometown. peter agrees and in an hour they are both on the most vibrant street in new york, awkwardly greeting each other.

how it ultimately ends with a trip on a ferry to the island of freedom - no one knows. just after a couple of cups of coffee and a quick snack, peter recalls the main attraction of new york and johnny, listening to his voice favorably, decides not to miss the chance, immediately stopping a taxi and pushing in it peter who nothing understand.

neither johnny nor peter can still behave at ease in the presence of each other, and therefore they are trying to hide the general embarrassment behind the unfunny jokes all the way. the taxi driver glances at them in the mirror with irritation, at some point asking them to shut up for at least a couple of minutes. they keep talking.

finally, johnny buys ferry tickets, and they almost immediately sit on it - lucky with time. at some point the sun peeps out and Peter drops his jacket, and johnny kindly agrees to carry it. he has never been to the statue of liberty and he is glad that his first time will be with his boyfriend.

while they take the elevator peter looks around him, holding his hands behind his back, and Johnny stands behind and watches the slight sneaking of his curls. people around pretend not to notice.

on the observation deck a lot of tourists. there are different voices and accents everywhere, camera clicks are heard. it was then that peter realizes that he didn’t take it with him from home but johnny’s presence quickly relaxes him and he stops thinking about it, just enjoying the view.

he will still have a chance to take a photo.

johnny stands next to peter, staring at the look of new york. no matter how huge the panoramic windows in his house are, the stretching landscape from a point far from the city cannot be compared with the view from there. the heart starts beating a little more often and johnny is not sure: it is because of the exciting emotions, or peter who is very close.

they simultaneously move forward.

peter’s lips are chapped, dry, and crawl over the tongue, giving away the taste of a recently eaten cheeseburger. johnny is also supple and warm with a peach flavor, because someone likes to use glitter too much. a kiss is timid, not at all short but it seems that the whole world freezes around them, and when they open even noisy tourists cannot spoil their mood. back they go hand in hand.

this kiss becomes something significant, they begin to see more often, until in the end they no longer represent life without each other. every year on the same day they go to the statue of liberty and celebrate their small but most important anniversary.

custom does not die over the years. even when they come and spend a stormy night, playing video games, johnny still wakes peter up at ten in the morning to catch the ferry. this time he brings with him flowers, dahlias, peter’s beloved, and after the kiss that johnny gives, they have to be very strong in their hands so as not to defile lady liberty.

in memory of the camera every year there are new types of new york and johny’s portraits.

so pass six years.

in the seventh year johnny comes alone.

he, as then, begins his way with times square. walks into starbucks, does not let the burger king in, ordering the cheapest cheeseburger that peter ate, and then catches a taxi. this time the taxi driver is silent.

on the ferry as usual a lot of people. the weather is rainy today - no one takes off their jackets.

on the observation deck tourists. don’t change with time, the statue of liberty, too. unless the price for a ticket grows up and the guide is not as positively charged as before.

johnny stops at the rail and looks out the window. the city no longer seems fascinating.

he stands there from noon until evening, paying no guards. in the hands of a bouquet of dahlias.

johnny opens the phone. on lokskrine their joint photo.

he’s leaving.

before the trip johnny kisses one flower and puts the whole bouquet on the water.

peter is no longer five and a half months.

johnny seems his too.
